---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Macroline — Just say what you ate."
  description="The AI-native macro tracker. Describe a meal, scan a barcode, or connect Claude. Every food has a verified source."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-text">
      <p class="eyebrow"><span class="pip" aria-hidden="true"></span> AI-native macro tracker</p>
      <h1>Just say what<br/>you ate.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Describe a meal, scan a barcode, or connect Claude. Every food has a
        verified source — so you can finally trust the numbers.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/macroline/id6765770579" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="badge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M16.5 1.6c0 1.1-.4 2.1-1.2 2.9-.9.95-2 1.5-3.1 1.4-.1-1.1.4-2.2 1.1-2.9.85-.9 2.1-1.5 3.2-1.4zM20.3 17c-.5 1.2-.8 1.7-1.5 2.7-1 1.5-2.4 3.3-4.1 3.3-1.5 0-1.9-1-3.9-1-2 0-2.4 1-3.9 1-1.7 0-3-1.7-4-3.1-2.7-4-3-8.6-1.3-11.1 1.2-1.7 3-2.7 4.8-2.7 1.8 0 2.9 1 4.4 1 1.4 0 2.3-1 4.4-1 1.6 0 3.3.9 4.5 2.4-3.9 2.2-3.3 7.8.6 9.3z"/></svg>
          <span class="badge-label"><span>Download on the</span><b>App Store</b></span>
        </a>
        <a href="/features" class="btn-ghost">See features</a>
      </div>
      <p class="cta-sub"><b>Free</b> tier with everything that matters · <b>Pro $4.99/mo</b> unlocks AI input + Claude · or use the <a href="https://my.macroline.app">web app</a></p>
    </div>

    <!-- Food-forward hero visual: a real food photo with the in-app "Today"
         card floating over the lower-left corner, light-themed to match the
         warm site. The photo is the LCP element, so it loads eager. -->
    <div class="hero-visual">
      <div class="hero-photo">
        <img
          src="/food/hero-salmon.jpg"
          alt="Grilled salmon with a fresh green salad, avocado, and lemon on a pale plate"
          width="800"
          height="1000"
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
        />
        <span class="ph-tag">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 9a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h2l1.5-2h7L19 7h2a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v9a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2z"/><circle cx="12" cy="13" r="3.5"/></svg>
          Sourced macros, every meal
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="float-card" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="fc-head">
          <span class="fc-label">Today</span>
          <span class="fc-cal">1,847<span> cal</span></span>
        </div>
        <div class="bar p"><i></i><b>Protein</b><em>142g</em></div>
        <div class="bar c"><i></i><b>Carbs</b><em>186g</em></div>
        <div class="bar f"><i></i><b>Fat</b><em>64g</em></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pillars">
    <article class="pillar a">
      <div class="pillar-icon">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="9" y="2" width="6" height="12" rx="3"/><path d="M5 11a7 7 0 0 0 14 0M12 18v4"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h2>Speak it. Log it.</h2>
      <p>"A chicken caesar wrap with extra parmesan and a coke." Macroline parses natural language, finds the right foods, and logs the right portions. Voice or text, your call.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="pillar b">
      <div class="pillar-icon">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="7"/><path d="m21 21-4.3-4.3"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h2>Honest data.</h2>
      <p>Every food links to its source — USDA, manufacturer pages, official restaurant nutrition. Tap any number to see where it came from. No more bad community entries with wrong macros.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="pillar c">
      <div class="pillar-icon">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 7V2M15 7V2M8 7h8v4a4 4 0 0 1-8 0zM12 15v7"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h2>Log from Claude. Or ChatGPT. Anywhere.</h2>
      <p>Macroline runs as an MCP server, so any modern AI assistant can log meals for you. Talk to Claude on your laptop, ChatGPT on your phone — it all lands in your diary.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <!-- Real food + provenance band — ties the food imagery to the moat:
       every pictured meal carries a Verified provenance chip. -->
  <section class="foodband">
    <div class="foodband-head">
      <h2>Real food. Real numbers.</h2>
      <p>Every meal you log carries a provenance tier and a citation — the warmth of real food, backed by data you can actually trust.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="food-grid">
      <figure class="food-cell">
        <img src="/food/oats.jpg" alt="Overnight oats with blueberries, raspberries, and honey" width="800" height="800" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption class="chip"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Verified</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="food-cell">
        <img src="/food/salad.jpg" alt="Colorful grain salad bowl with sweet potato, chickpeas, and tahini" width="800" height="800" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption class="chip"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Verified</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="food-cell">
        <img src="/food/chicken.jpg" alt="Grilled chicken over rice with broccoli and roasted peppers" width="800" height="800" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption class="chip"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Verified</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="food-cell">
        <img src="/food/smoothie.jpg" alt="Green smoothie with almonds, banana, spinach, and kiwi" width="800" height="800" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption class="chip"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Verified</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="moat">
    <h2>Every number, sourced.</h2>
    <p class="moat-lede">
      Macroline is built on a different principle than most trackers: <strong>show your work.</strong>
      Every food row in our database carries a provenance tier and a citation URL.
    </p>
    <div class="tier-grid">
      <div class="tier authoritative">
        <span class="tier-dot"></span>
        <h3>Authoritative</h3>
        <p>USDA FoodData Central, manufacturer pages, official chain restaurant nutrition. The gold standard.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tier computed">
        <span class="tier-dot"></span>
        <h3>Computed</h3>
        <p>Recipe foods derived from authoritative ingredients with summed macros. Math is verifiable.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tier estimated">
        <span class="tier-dot"></span>
        <h3>Estimated</h3>
        <p>AI-researched from cross-checked sources when no official data exists. Cited and flagged.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tier unverified">
        <span class="tier-dot"></span>
        <h3>Unverified</h3>
        <p>User-submitted entries, awaiting community confirmation. Visible but never silently trusted.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy promises strip — surfaces what's deep on /privacy. One of
       the strongest trust signals available; was hidden three clicks deep. -->
  <section class="promises">
    <p class="promises-label">Our promises</p>
    <div class="promises-grid">
      <article class="promise promise-protein">
        <span class="promise-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2 4 5v6c0 5 3.5 8.5 8 11 4.5-2.5 8-6 8-11V5z"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Never sold</h3>
        <p>Your data isn't a product.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="promise promise-carbs">
        <span class="promise-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="m5.6 5.6 12.8 12.8"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Never trained</h3>
        <p>We don't feed your meals to AI models.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="promise promise-fat">
        <span class="promise-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3v12m0 0 4-4m-4 4-4-4M5 21h14"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Export anytime</h3>
        <p>CSV + JSON, your whole history.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="promise promise-accent">
        <span class="promise-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 7h16M9 7V5a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h4a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v2m-9 0 1 13h10l1-13"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Delete in one tap</h3>
        <p>Cascades through every record.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder note — the site had no human anywhere. This is the single
       highest-impact warmth fix for a category as personal as nutrition. -->
  <section class="founder">
    <div class="founder-photo">
      <img
        src="/founder.jpg"
        alt="Mike — Macroline founder"
        loading="lazy"
        width="220"
        height="280"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="founder-text">
      <h2>Built by one person who got tired of bad food data.</h2>
      <p>
        I'm Mike. I built Macroline because every macro tracker I tried lied to me — bad
        community entries, wrong serving sizes, "estimates" that were guesses. The whole
        product is one bet: if every number can be traced to a real source, people will trust it.
      </p>
      <p>
        If something's off, I read the support inbox personally. Email me anytime at
        <a href="mailto:info@macroline.app">info@macroline.app</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="founder-sig">— Mike, founder</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="download" class="download">
    <h2>Macroline is on the App Store.</h2>
    <p>Free to download, with everything that matters in the free tier. Pro ($4.99/mo) unlocks AI meal logging and the Claude integration.</p>
    <a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/macroline/id6765770579" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="appstore-cta">
      Download on the App Store →
    </a>
    <p class="download-or">No iPhone? The full app runs in your browser at <a href="https://my.macroline.app">my.macroline.app</a>.</p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Bright, warm, food-forward hero. Full-bleed warm gradient with a soft
     carbs-yellow glow top-right and a fresh-green glow bottom-left (was the
     dark navy band); re-constrains its inner content to the page width. */
  .hero {
    margin-inline: calc(50% - 50vw);
    padding-inline: max(24px, calc(50vw - 550px));
    padding-block: 64px 56px;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 760px 520px at 88% -6%, rgba(242, 183, 5, 0.18) 0%, transparent 58%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 620px 480px at -4% 108%, rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.14) 0%, transparent 60%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #FFFDF8 0%, var(--bg) 100%);
    color: var(--text);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 0.95fr;
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding-block: 48px 40px; }
    .hero-text { text-align: center; }
    .cta-row { justify-content: center; }
  }
  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--fresh);
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  .eyebrow .pip { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--fresh); }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 68px);
    line-height: 1.0;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 22px 0 0;
    max-width: 500px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 30px;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  /* Apple App Store badge — navy pill, the brand anchor against the warm hero. */
  .badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 11px;
    background: var(--navy);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 13px 22px;
    border-radius: var(--r-pill);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .badge:hover { background: #13233f; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; }
  .badge svg { width: 22px; height: 22px; }
  .badge-label { display: flex; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.1; text-align: left; }
  .badge-label span { font-size: 10px; opacity: 0.8; font-weight: 500; }
  .badge-label b { font-size: 16px; }
  .btn-ghost {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 15px;
    padding: 13px 18px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-pill);
    background: var(--surface);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .btn-ghost:hover { background: var(--surface-2); text-decoration: none; }
  .cta-sub { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 13px; margin-top: 18px; max-width: 500px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .cta-sub b { color: var(--text); }
  .cta-sub a { color: var(--fresh); }

  /* Hero visual — food photo with the in-app "Today" card floating over the
     lower-left corner, light-themed to match the warm site. */
  .hero-visual { position: relative; min-height: 440px; }
  @media (max-width: 880px) { .hero-visual { min-height: 0; margin-top: 8px; } }
  .hero-photo {
    position: relative;
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    max-width: 380px;
    margin-left: auto;
    /* Gradient under the photo — also the placeholder tint until the real
       AI food photo lands at /food/hero-salmon.jpg. */
    background: linear-gradient(150deg, #2f7d4f 0%, #6aa84f 42%, #d9b44a 100%);
  }
  .hero-photo img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block; }
  .ph-tag {
    position: absolute;
    left: 12px;
    bottom: 12px;
    background: rgba(10, 22, 40, 0.72);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 11px;
    padding: 5px 10px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    display: inline-flex;
    gap: 6px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .ph-tag svg { width: 12px; height: 12px; opacity: 0.85; }
  .float-card {
    position: absolute;
    left: -8px;
    bottom: 36px;
    width: 268px;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .hero-photo { margin: 0 auto; }
    .float-card { left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); bottom: -18px; width: min(268px, 88%); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .float-card { position: static; transform: none; width: 100%; margin: 14px auto 0; }
  }
  .fc-head { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .fc-label { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 700; }
  .fc-cal { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--text); }
  .fc-cal span { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500; }
  .bar {
    height: 24px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: var(--surface-2);
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 0 11px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    overflow: hidden;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .bar i { position: absolute; inset: 0 auto 0 0; border-radius: 12px; }
  .bar.p i { width: 78%; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--protein) 80%, #fff); }
  .bar.c i { width: 62%; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--carbs) 80%, #fff); }
  .bar.f i { width: 54%; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fat) 75%, #fff); }
  .bar b, .bar em { position: relative; z-index: 1; font-style: normal; }
  .bar em { font-family: ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', monospace; }

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 84px;
  }
  .pillar {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    padding: 30px 26px;
    position: relative;
  }
  /* 3px colored top-accent per card. */
  .pillar::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 26px;
    right: 26px;
    height: 3px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .pillar.a::before { background: var(--protein); }
  .pillar.b::before { background: var(--fresh); }
  .pillar.c::before { background: var(--fat); }
  /* Real line icons in colored rounded chips (was emoji). */
  .pillar-icon {
    width: 46px;
    height: 46px;
    border-radius: 13px;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .pillar-icon svg { width: 24px; height: 24px; }
  .pillar.a .pillar-icon { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--protein) 14%, #fff); color: var(--protein); }
  .pillar.b .pillar-icon { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fresh) 14%, #fff); color: var(--fresh); }
  .pillar.c .pillar-icon { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fat) 14%, #fff); color: var(--fat); }
  .pillar h2 { font-size: 21px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .pillar p { color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }

  /* Real food + provenance band — 4-up square photos, each with a Verified
     provenance chip tying the imagery back to the moat. */
  .foodband { margin-top: 84px; }
  .foodband-head { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .foodband-head h2 { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px); }
  .foodband-head p { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 17px; margin: 14px auto 0; max-width: 560px; }
  .food-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .food-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
  .food-cell {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0;
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    /* Placeholder tint until the real AI food photo lands at /food/*. */
    background: linear-gradient(150deg, #3f8f5a, #86c06a);
  }
  .food-cell img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block; }
  .food-cell .chip {
    position: absolute;
    left: 10px;
    top: 10px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
    color: #0f5132;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 4px 9px;
    border-radius: 7px;
    display: inline-flex;
    gap: 5px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .food-cell .chip .dot { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--fresh); }

  .moat {
    margin-top: 100px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .moat h2 { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); }
  .moat-lede { color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 600px; margin: 16px auto 40px; font-size: 17px; }
  .tier-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .tier-grid .tier {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    padding: 20px;
    font-size: inherit;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: normal;
    font-weight: normal;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .tier-grid .tier h3 { font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tier-grid .tier p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0; }
  .tier-dot {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .tier-grid .authoritative .tier-dot { background: #10B981; }
  .tier-grid .computed     .tier-dot { background: #3B82F6; }
  .tier-grid .estimated    .tier-dot { background: #EAB308; }
  .tier-grid .unverified   .tier-dot { background: #94A3B8; }

  /* Privacy promises strip — surfaces the /privacy commitments. 4-up
     desktop / 2x2 tablet / 1-col mobile. Icon chips use the macro
     palette (protein/carbs/fat/accent) so it picks up the brand. */
  .promises {
    margin-top: 100px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .promises-label {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }
  .promises-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    text-align: left;
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .promises-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .promises-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .promise {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .promise-icon {
    display: inline-grid;
    place-items: center;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .promise-icon svg { width: 18px; height: 18px; }
  .promise-protein .promise-icon { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--protein) 16%, transparent); color: var(--protein); }
